Classes in it.unipr.ce.dsg.deus.core used by it.unipr.ce.dsg.deus.core
Engine
           This class represents the simulation engine of DEUS.
Event
           The Event class represents the simulation object being scheduled by the Engine.
InvalidParamsException
          This class represents the exceptions thrown in case the parameters passed to simulation objects are wrong.
Node
           The Node class represents the "entity" inside the simulation.
Process
           The Process class represents the simulation object responsible to determine the timing of events scheduling.
Resource
          This class represent the generic resource associated to a node.
RunException
          This class represents the exceptions thrown in case the run method of simulation events fails.
SchedulerListener
          This interface is used to implement a listening method that event can use to be notified when one of their referenced event is scheduled for the execution.
SimulationException
          This class represents the exceptions thrown in case one of the components into the simulation fails its execution.
SimulationObject
          Class used to abstract each simulation object, adding the member and methods to support the logging process.
